history.content: I took 162 + 168 + 186.  I didn't do exceptionally well in any of the classes but I blame it on my inability to focus and inability to just grind out the work.  I think it's "manageable" especially if you have a good team for 162.  I consider myself really lucky in having a solid 162 group and an awesome 168 project partner.  Honestly anything is doable if you're willing to sacrifice and just give it all you got

children.subject:
Trust me 162 will be much much much more manageable with a good group. The hardest part of the class IMO is the projects and they are a pretty huge chunk of your grade compared to other classes. 

I honestly think you can do the 168 projects on your own (except maybe the last one). Having a partner definitely makes things easier but the projects are in Python and are fairly manageable if you start early.
Got it, thanks! (especially for the emphasis on a good group for 162) :)
Thanks - 162 looks hard even with a great group, so how about the workload for 168 (if you had a decent partner)?
